{
  "texts": [
    "Fixed proposal scales may lead to missing small objects, and ROI pooling on sparse proposals can result in losing spatial details.",
    "The separate training of the RPN and detection network components also hinders optimization.",
    "Moreover, these models lack inherent feature enhancement mechanisms for handling visually similar classes.",
    "In contrast, YOLOv8-CAB overcomes these limitations using a single-stage YOLOv8-CAB enhanced detection approach with multi-scale feature processing, enabling faster and more accurate detection, especially for small and visually similar objects.In 2018, A. Wong and M. Javad developed Tiny SSD [34], a concise deep neural network structure for real-time embedded object detection.",
    "This method utilizes Fire modules inspired by Squeeze Net and auxiliary convolutions based on the single shot detector architecture to reduce model size while maintaining accuracy."
  ]
}